original &#34;L&#34; horizontally so that the new form starts on the upper 
parallel and ends on the lower parallel instead of vice versa like the 
original &#34;L&#34;.&#160; Now, using this alternate &#34;L&#34;, writing &#34;flight&#34; becomes:&#160;

a letter &#34;F&#34;, &lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;NO penlift&lt;/span&gt;, an alternate letter &#34;L&#34;, &lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;NO penlift&lt;/span&gt;, a Letter 
31 (&#34;m&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;y&lt;/span&gt;&#34;), and the final &#34;T&#34;.&#160; As with the alternate letter &#34;N&#34; which 
